/**
 * eyetracking.ts -- Gnosis-native eye-tracking corpus and failure semantics
 *
 * Eye tracking is treated as an append-only rejection surface:
 *   - observations are the witness stream
 *   - calibration is a finite cave with explicit deficit
 *   - failures are vents that grow a VoidBoundary
 *   - the failure log is Merkle-verifiable
 *   - the session is replayable through QDoc
 *
 * This makes eye-tracking failures first-class training data for Dash,
 * Neural, void-os, and downstream ETaaS services without introducing a
 * second semantics layer outside gnosis.
 */

